text.tspan: This figure shows our model of the oral epithelium during HHV8 infection. Virus
reactivates from latently infected cells. The infection spreads from cell-to-cell
via cell-associated virus. T cells respond to the infection by killing infected cells. Infected
cells also die at a faster rate than susceptible cells. Upon a cell's death, its cell-associated
virus is released as extra-cellular virus which is available for collection during daily
swabbing. Multiple, independent regions of infection may be spreading concurrently.
